<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11280105-jennifer-gargiulo"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1612904872i/11280105._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11280105-jennifer-gargiulo">Jennifer Gargiulo</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s that eventually she wouldn&apos;t be able to see him/hear him/interact with him. So that&apos;s not an actual relationship. I guess the point is that he lo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's that eventually she wouldn't be able to see him/hear him/interact with him. So that's not an actual relationship. I guess the point is that he loved her so much that he didn't want to put her in a situation where her life stagnates again-just like the old man's did when Olivia showed Ivan her love.<br /><br />I agree with the other answerer. I don't think that there is any implication that she ends up with Benjamin-more that she's changed from an uptight person to someone more relaxed and fun thanks to Ivan.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
